{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17656966","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17656966"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:21:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:21:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18975"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18975","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18975"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0,0,0.93,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11709"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80701"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11709","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11709"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18975"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66000"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"147"},{"type":"tags","id":"1284"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4956"},{"type":"tags","id":"4986"},{"type":"tags","id":"4989"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"11348"},{"type":"tags","id":"11382"},{"type":"tags","id":"11421"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11645"},{"type":"tags","id":"11648"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27555"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40309"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80701","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80701"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with her support worker for review of her asthma. She has mild intellectual disability but lives independently with support. Her medical history includes well-controlled asthma. Her medications include salbutamol and fluticasone inhalers. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate communication approach?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Defer all decisions to the support worker","Direct all questions and explanations to the support worker","Communicate only through written instructions","Use simplified language and speak directly to the patient","Speak loudly and slowly to ensure understanding"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUsing simplified language and speaking directly to the patient\u003C/strong\u003E maintains dignity and autonomy while ensuring effective communication. Plain language should be used without being patronising, and questions should be directed to the patient first.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirecting all questions and explanations to the support worker\u003C/strong\u003E inappropriately excludes the patient from their own healthcare decisions. While the support worker can provide valuable information, the patient should be the primary focus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECommunicating only through written instructions\u003C/strong\u003E- a multi-modal approach combining verbal explanation with visual aids is often most effective\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESpeaking loudly and slowly\u003C/strong\u003E is inappropriate and potentially demeaning. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDeferring all decisions to the support worker\u003C/strong\u003E fails to respect the patient\u0027s right to be involved in their own healthcare decisions. The support worker\u0027s role is to assist and advocate, not to replace the patient\u0027s autonomy. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Communication with patients who have intellectual disabilities should be direct and age-appropriate, avoiding infantilising language.","Carers should be included in discussions while maintaining the patient\u0027s autonomy and dignity.","Complex medical information should be presented clearly using plain language and visual aids when appropriate."],"references":["Agaronnik N, Campbell EG, Ressalam J, Iezzoni LI. Communicating with Patients with Disability: Perspectives of Practicing Physicians. J Gen Intern Med. 2019;34(7):1139-1145. doi:10.1007/s11606-019-04911-0"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66000"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18975"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66000","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/66000"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-22T14:39:50+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-06T16:48:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11709"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80701"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}